Class RPNNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • aprove.Framework.IntTRS.Nonterm.GeoNonTerm.ReversePolishNotationTree.RPNNode
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    RPNConstant, RPNFunctionSymbol, RPNVariable

    public abstract class RPNNode
extends java.lang.Object
    The RPNNode is an abstract node in the binary RPNTree (reverse polish notation tree).
    The subclasses are RPNConstant, RPNVariable and RPNFunctionSymbol
    Author:
    Timo Bergerbusch
    See Also:
    RPNConstant, RPNVariable, RPNFunctionSymbol

      • getFactorOfVar

        public int getFactorOfVar(java.lang.String varName)
        This method derives the factors of the given variable within the tree using the following recursive algorithm:
        1. checks whether it is a RPNVariable or a RPNConstant, which both have no following RPNNode's and the value can be obviously derived
        2. for a RPNFunctionSymbol it distinguishes between the three different ArithmeticSymbol's:
          • ArithmeticSymbol.TIMES: derives the factor recursively within the child RPNNode that does not contain the variable, because if would not contain the factor
          • ArithmeticSymbol.LESS_THAN/ArithmeticSymbol.GREATER_THAN/ArithmeticSymbol.PLUS: derives the factor within the child that contains the var and can neglect the other child, because of syntax reasons (more below)
          • ArithmeticSymbol.MINUS: same as for ArithmeticSymbol.PLUS, but changes the result by negating the factor, because of the -
          • if non of the other hold's the method returns 0

        The assumtion the method makes is that the terms are linear and flattened. So 2*(a+b) would be 2*a+2*b
        Parameters:
        varName - the name of the variable of which the factor should be derived
        Returns:
        the factor of the parameter variable or 0
        See Also:
        containsVar(String)

      • getConstantTerm

        public int getConstantTerm()
        this method derives the constant term within a RPNTree. If two child nodes containt a constant (should never happen) they get added.
        Returns:
        the constant term( 0 by default)
